messages.message: If you define multiple fetchers in a scripts directory, which one gets executed? Just curious
with UDFs named the same thing, it’s whichever was read last (usually the one in the last file alphabetically)

not named the same thing. In the Fetch Files step in Flow, there’s nowhere for you to specify which class to invoke for the fetcher, so I assumed it just executes one in the scripts dir, but not sure which one.
